##A gym instructor decided to make a delivery

Micro Signal thelivings

The function introduction, reconstructs our life with the narrative beauty.

On February 11, I ran my first 35 runs; yesterday, I was Lucky, I ran 41; next month, I'm going to start my own savings plan, saving at least 5,000 yuan a month.

"I feel like I'm being pushed to the breaking point of my own money chain. "
Rayong, a 25 year old Thai boxing coach in Foshan, is worried. He used to go to the gym to lift iron or to fight someone. Not this time. Under the epidemic, the gym has been closed, no income, every month he has to pay 5000 yuan consumer loans.
This kind of anguish, rely on exercise only to eliminate, completely to no avail. On Jan. 25, he registered with Rayong as Meituan crowdsourced rider, a temporary food delivery service. Run a single to earn a single money, the first day of running, the next day to receive money.
Unlike the usual cyclists who ride their electric bikes through shops and neighborhoods, Rayong makes deliveries on his "dead fly" bike, pedaling his food as fast as he can and standing up for fear of losing a few dollars on a long, wasted trip, pedal breathless, even more tired than usual exercise, "this is called forced life. ".
In Guangzhou, a 40-minute drive from Foshan, 21-year-old Pan Junchao decided to become a ride-along, also because the working gym was slow to open. During the epidemic, people around the quarantine, road closure, the old provincial riders back to work blocked, but also in his hometown of Shaoguan Pan Junchao in the station chief under a series of calls, early return to Guangzhou to join, began his own as a rider "internship. ".
In Guangzhou in February, when the temperature was around 20 degrees Celsius, pan junchao rode his newly acquired little donkeys through the streets and alleys, entering and leaving various kinds of residential areas, and saw all kinds of scenery. As he passed the Pearl River, the moist breeze that carried the water vapor swept over his face and made him feel comfortable, very happy, like traveling.
In this way, two young post 95 fitness coaches, whether forced to save themselves or actively transform themselves, are experiencing a different kind of professional bitterness and joy —— as if it were a microcosm of the shift in employment patterns in China during the epidemic.
Data from Meituan show that from January 20 to February 23,2020,75,000 workers became their riders, a steady increase. Of the new riders, 37.6 percent are from the lifestyle services industry, like the pair.

"I'm afraid I'm the only biker in Foshan delivering food. "
@ Xiang Rayong, born in 1995, now lives in Foshan

I'm afraid I'm the only bike delivery rider in Foshan. How do I feel? In a word, it was as difficult for me as it was for me.
My girlfriend and I used to work in the same gym, and we were both trainers. We used to work after the Spring Festival, and at the latest after the Fifteenth Day of the first lunar month. Because of the epidemic, the normal working hours were delayed, only said that March can start, but the specific date can work, the boss did not say.
My girlfriend and I both feel that starting a job is a bit of a long shot, so let's find some part-time jobs that make money first.
First Day on the job, first delivery, pizza delivery. I rode off on my bike with a camo backpack from my old army days. The owner of the pizza place looked at me in all my gear, said I couldn't put the pizza on its side, and scrambled to get me a take-out box.
That day, I drove the pizza shop owner's homemade delivery box to deliver five orders.
After delivering my last order, it started to rain, so I went back to the pizza place, returned the delivery box, and pedaled back to my dorm. May Be a breath to ride more than 2 hours did not stop, pedal pedal pedal, "PA" , a tire on the burst.
I was three Klicks away from where I lived. What do I do? Keep pedaling.
Luckily, I was riding a dead horse, with a small wheel and a flat tire. As it turns out, the more you push, the heavier it gets. On second thought, it wasn't worth it -- a pair of tires cost over $100 -- and I only made over $50 that day.
The next day, I had a delivery, and it was pizza, and the destination was weird, and before I could find a place, the order ran over, and it was a waste of time, and it cost me eight dollars to run the errand.
A few days later, I did not go, coupled with the previous two days by the "blow" , a little do not want to go to the delivery. Girlfriend see me like this, they give me to do ideological work, said a sentence: "Alas, we are not working, do not go to work, need to live AH, hard. "
My Heart said, ok, I try a little bit, to earn money, after all, I still have more than 50,000 foreign debt, every month to pay more than 5000 bank loans, no money to renew, very nervous.
To suppress the feelings of resistance, after the delivery seems to be more smooth. On the worst days, there were more orders, fewer riders, half a day's worth of outdoor work, and I was on sixteen legs, as it was hard to get orders, two or three riders in front of a store, all on electric bikes, how can a guy on a bike like me survive? Fortunately, I have some old students at home hold too long, I took the initiative to take classes.
Riders waiting for their order at the door
Crowdsourcing isn't a particularly good way for me to increase my income, mainly because I can't get long distance orders on my bike, so I have to pick up and drop off three or five yuan orders to the nearest location, usually two or three kilometers away. I would also take a couple of "on-the-way" orders at the same time, but that was a risk. If one restaurant was slow, it could lead to late orders for the rest of the trip, and basically the whole list would go to waste.

One time, I got a "waybill" . It was a close call. That day I took two orders at the same time "Wallace" , the destination is about 2 km away from the store, but direction in the opposite direction, fortunately enough time.
I didn't expect it would take more than 10 minutes. And while I was waiting, I got two orders coming in, and the food wasn't ready, leaving me five minutes less than I thought it would be, Florida, which was killing me.
Well, if that's the case, then pedal faster!
When it was ready, I picked it up and sprinted out. One from the north arrived, and one from the south went wrong, heading off-course again, in Florida, because of the outbreak, the roads were blocked everywhere, and the cell phone route wasn't working, so we had to take the long way. Time is more tense, I directly stand up to step on the pedal, speed twice as fast as usual, pedal I can not breathe.
When we got to the south, there was about a minute to go before the appointed time, and I called, out of breath, to let the customers come and get their food. When I handed over my food, it was 30 seconds to go, as if I wasn't so nervous as I was when I was in the army, fighting for my life.
In fact, this one is only five or six dollars, but for me, through the efforts of the money is very precious.
I joined the army in Nanking when I was 17. I was in the army for five years. After I got out of the Army, a gym teacher asked me if I wanted to be a trainer, so I took it for three months, then Thai boxing in Bangkok.
I've been to a lot of cities for work. After leaving the army in Nanjing, I came to Guangdong, first Foshan, then to Guangzhou and Shenzhen, where I stayed in many gyms and gyms, including the famous chain Foshan. After all, people want to go to higher places.
Now back in Foshan, the gym where I work is still the same one I started in Guangdong.
After all this time, this is the place for me. Although our gym also speak sales commission, but professional high, not so much sales performance appraisal, for me to take the professional line of low-key coach. And this gym is also more humane. Coaches and members can easily get along. Members come from nearby computer factories and mechanical cities. Some work here, some open their own shops, and our membership fees are very cheap, most people can afford it.
Working in the gym, the main income is to take private lessons, teaching people to use Thai boxing fat loss body, but also take some children play Thai boxing. A private teaching is 300 yuan, but, income is very volatile, like winter vacation, about class, I can get more than 10,000 a month salary, low time also took 3,000 or 4,000 yuan.
As a fitness instructor, you can earn money with peace of mind. If you take classes and spend time, you can get a commission at the end of the month. But as a rider, it's different. If you make a sum of money after a run, you will see the income immediately. If you run for nothing, you will have no money, the "result-oriented" effect is so strong that it forces you to get nervous on your own.
I didn't make a lot of money during this time, but it was enough to make me feel that life was hard for me -- as a former coach, I was surrounded by people who spent a lot of time with them, and I was motivated to spend a lot After being a horseman, I just feel, even if it is a dollar, also want to cherish, that is to pay sweat to earn.
So, I haven't cashed out any of the cash from the rider account, so I'll just take it out when I need it.
I've been in Foshan for over a year, and I've been training in Guangzhou and taking fitness classes with Daliang Subdistrict, so I think I'm going to be heading into a new phase of my life -- as a rider. After all, every single run, earn 2030 dollars, just enough to ensure that my day's living, I can run after work for two hours, from 10 to 12.
I plan to save up this year to buy a bike that can be ridden and delivered, so that I can live on it -- I'm ashamed to say that everything I do now seems to be falling into my lap. Before I am very disdainful to do micro-commerce to sell sports supplements, think this will affect a coach's degree of professionalism, but, these days I re-advertising, or life is forced.
Funny thing is, my mom found out I was delivering food and said, if you're a rider, you can come back home and do it. My hometown is in Hengyang City of Hunan Province under the small county of Foshan of course, I am not a obedient mother of people, even if I go back, I would choose Changsha.
When I'm too old to be a trainer, it might be a good idea to consider becoming a full-time rider.

"I'm so happy. I didn't know delivery was so much fun. "
@ Pan Junchao was born in 1999 and now lives in Guangzhou

I'm kind of a slow starter. When I was a fitness instructor, I found it hard to talk to strangers.
There are two types of trainers: A personal trainer who has to speak as if he were selling his skills, and a group drill instructor who earns more than 100 dollars per class. I got into this business purely as a The Wrong Mans, and at first I didn't know anything about it, except that I liked to work out with my hands, and I just kept going online. Later, I went to the fitness institute to learn how to do a personal trainer, how to lead the group calisthenics, learned for 2 months, to apply for the coach.
There are hundreds of gyms in Guangzhou. Before I went to work, I joined a part-time group of group gymnastics coaches. Many gyms would recruit group gymnastics coaches to take classes there. As soon as I saw the recruitment information, I took a job and rode the subway all over Guangzhou. It can be said that I have been to almost all of the 154 stations of the 11 subways in Guangzhou.
Working in the gym, I can exercise every day, I am very happy, the only thing is not good, I do not do sales, it may be too little experience with me, and also do not know what communication skills, always sell classes.
But the only way to survive at the gym is to sell. It's a lot of pressure without results. The company also has a ranking, top ranked colleagues, a month can have one hundred thousand results, while I have only a little, and sometimes will be named and criticized by the leadership. Every day in such an environment, I feel very depressed, in the group exercise class on the stage has become less and less self-confidence.
I know I've been avoiding the sales thing. My hometown in Shaoguan, Guangdong, junior high school did not graduate, I came to Guangzhou to study a secondary technical school, is "computer network applications" , 3 years after graduation, the school introduced me to a telephone sales work. I went over there, stayed for about half a month, and then I realized it wasn't really for me.
I thought I could just do what I love, but I still have to "sell" . Now, this career is essentially a combination of service and sales.
In October last year, I really couldn't do business in the gym. I happened to have a friend who does "digital currency" . I saw the profits were high and quit my job to work with him. I made 50,000 yuan in the first month, but I wasn't happy for long, the next month, it's gone, plus interest.
At that time, I stay at home every day, very decadent, do not know what to do, mind a blank. By January, I was determined to fight it -- but I didn't have a good degree, and I didn't want to be in sales. What could I do?
On second thought, I thought I'd give delivery a try.
In fact, I did not intend to start so early, when the epidemic situation is still very serious, parents do not agree with me to return to Guangzhou early. However, the Dashi Station stationmaster kept calling me, said they are very short of people, I promised my parents, will protect themselves, returned to Guangzhou.

On February 7th, I officially started delivering food, and my internship was for a month. The first day as a rider, Guangzhou felt like an empty city, dark at night, only street lights. Think if it is not an epidemic, the usual evening, there will always be a variety of food stalls on the road, lively.
But this kind of Guangzhou, in the daytime will not affect my mood.
I used to spend every day in the gym, staring at the members, never had a chance to go out, and never thought delivery would be so much fun, as if I were riding around on a little donkey electric bike, looking at all kinds of scenery. Our station is very close to Changlong Zoo, and the view of many residential areas is very good. Sitting on a small donkey blowing river wind, feel comfortable —— This is sitting in the office to blow air-conditioned people can enjoy the joy of a holiday.
Riding around the city on a little donkey scooter
On my first day, however, I lost $20 because one of my meals was not properly secured before delivery and spilled on the way. I told my guest, "I'm sorry. It was a bumpy ride. ". He didn't say anything when he picked up the food, and when I was far away, he called me and said, "it's really hard to eat. ". I compensated him for the original price, after all, this is my personal responsibility, it should be compensated.

Then one day in the evening rush hour, I ran a single ran out of electricity, but this time came two new orders, a vegetable, a pile of cooked vegetables and a large watermelon. I didn't have time to charge it, so I set off on the mule's foot, which slowed me down a lot, and by the time the second order arrived, it was 30 minutes overdue.
Midway, I called the guest three times: The first call did not get through; the second he answered, very impatient, let me hurry; the third call, he was angry, said, "let me go downstairs to look, if the food cold, I will return. ".
When I heard him say this, I felt as if it had been cold for so long. This order is very expensive, I also took a special look at the time of delivery, about 150 yuan. I arrived at the place, and so on the guests downstairs, subliminally touched the take-out bag with his hand, ok, warm, not cold. I said, sir, it's still warm. The guy didn't say anything. He took the takeout. I was relieved.
In this case, if the other party insisted on compensation, I can only admit defeat, because the guests can not understand what kind of emergency you encountered, you stepped on the donkey tired, they do not know.
"It's okay to overtime your internship, and the system won't charge you for it, " Harvard, my master told me. The day before I took up my post, the station master arranged a master for me. I asked him all the questions I didn't understand. Master told me to take one order after another, take your time, get familiar with the route, and above all, "no bad reviews or complaints. ".
I took down the master's words, from the 7th to now, not only no bad comments, but also received several tips, not much money, usually 8.8 or 6.6. It made a lot of sense to me -- as if I'd been at the gym with a member who lost weight and was happier than they were. This is my moment to be valued, to be recognized.
Over the same period before I started or after the beginning of the new trainee riders, have complaints and bad reviews, I can do not, of course, not because I am handsome, but mainly service attitude.
For more than half a month, as I rode through the alley on my mule, I would hear other delivery boys on the phone, and they would say something like this: "Hey, your delivery has arrived, you can come down. " After the guests came down, they handed the delivery to the guests, didn't say anything, just left. After all, I used to be a fitness instructor, in the service industry, and I pay a lot of attention to polite words when communicating with my members. When I talk to guests, I always say things like "thank you" , "enjoy your meal" or "it's been a while" . I also take out the trash for them.
We usually go to work at 10 am and leave at 8 pm. My colleague who started two days before me told me that he only works 8 hours a day, whether he is single or not. But I can't leave at 8:00 every night, and I usually stay up past 10:00. I set myself a small goal -- I'm a Taurus -- to reach 35 a day. I'm always counting my money, and I only make $8,000 at the end of the month if I make 33 a day.
Right now, I'm happy with the way I'm doing my job. I'm sure there are difficulties, but there are more ways. I made more as a rider than I did at the gym. At the peak, I was making 6,000 or 7,000 a month. At the low end, it was just over 4,000. Used to envy others high wages, but very confused, do not know how to do, now every day is very down-to-earth, clear goals, "do" it.
On February 11th, I made my first 35 runs. Lucky for me, I had 41 jobs yesterday. Next month, I'll start my own savings plan, saving at least 5,000 yuan a month.
Even if the clock is ticking, we still have to undergo rigorous disinfection and temperature testing before picking up our meals
Guangzhou is a big city. I want to find my own place.

I had a girlfriend, very beautiful girl, 4 years older than me, family is also very good, in Guangzhou have a car and house. I always felt inferior with her. I wanted to give her the best, but I couldn't. I had a great month investing in digital currencies last year, making money, thinking I'd finally be able to plan my future with her, but this beautiful vision quickly faded, and I never dared to see her again -- for her sake, I should leave her.
Years ago, I sent her Wechat, do not want to waste her youth, do not want to drag her again. On February 14, Valentine's Day, she couldn't resist texting me with a bunch of "will wait for me" messages. But I was afraid to give her any commitment, just want to make a good money, to complete a small daily take-out tasks, monthly savings goals, and then can buy a house in 2.5 years or 3 years, Florida City can not afford to buy a house, peripheral can see, for example, Conghua District, the price as long as ten thousand and seven, now from Guangzhou in the past also have the subway, very convenient.
When I first came to Guangzhou, I saw the "small waist" for the first time and thought, how can there be such a tall and beautiful tower? I was also surprised to see Zhujiang New Town and thought the buildings there were so beautiful.
I have not been anywhere else, I feel good Guangzhou, if possible, I certainly hope to take root here.
As much as I enjoy riding a donkey on a deserted road, I prefer Guangzhou, which is full of people. I really hope that the day of normalcy comes soon.

Soph
An active city watcher

When we got to the south, there was about a minute to go before the appointed time, and I called, out of breath, to let the customers come and get their food. When I handed over my food, it was 30 seconds to go, as if I wasn't so nervous as I was when I was in the army, fighting for my life.
In fact, this one is only five or six dollars, but for me, through the efforts of the money is very precious.
I joined the army in Nanking when I was 17. I was in the army for five years. After I got out of the Army, a gym teacher asked me if I wanted to be a trainer, so I took it for three months, then Thai boxing in Bangkok.
I've been to a lot of cities for work. After leaving the army in Nanjing, I came to Guangdong, first Foshan, then to Guangzhou and Shenzhen, where I stayed in many gyms and gyms, including the famous chain Foshan. After all, people want to go to higher places.
Now back in Foshan, the gym where I work is still the same one I started in Guangdong.
After all this time, this is the place for me. Although our gym also speak sales commission, but professional high, not so much sales performance appraisal, for me to take the professional line of low-key coach. And this gym is also more humane. Coaches and members can easily get along. Members come from nearby computer factories and mechanical cities. Some work here, some open their own shops, and our membership fees are very cheap, most people can afford it.
Working in the gym, the main income is to take private lessons, teaching people to use Thai boxing fat loss body, but also take some children play Thai boxing. A private teaching is 300 yuan, but, income is very volatile, like winter vacation, about class, I can get more than 10,000 a month salary, low time also took 3,000 or 4,000 yuan.
As a fitness instructor, you can earn money with peace of mind. If you take classes and spend time, you can get a commission at the end of the month. But as a rider, it's different. If you make a sum of money after a run, you will see the income immediately. If you run for nothing, you will have no money, the "result-oriented" effect is so strong that it forces you to get nervous on your own.
I didn't make a lot of money during this time, but it was enough to make me feel that life was hard for me -- as a former coach, I was surrounded by people who spent a lot of time with them, and I was motivated to spend a lot After being a horseman, I just feel, even if it is a dollar, also want to cherish, that is to pay sweat to earn.
So, I haven't cashed out any of the cash from the rider account, so I'll just take it out when I need it.
I've been in Foshan for over a year, and I've been training in Guangzhou and taking fitness classes with Daliang Subdistrict, so I think I'm going to be heading into a new phase of my life -- as a rider. After all, every single run, earn 2030 dollars, just enough to ensure that my day's living, I can run after work for two hours, from 10 to 12.
I plan to save up this year to buy a bike that can be ridden and delivered, so that I can live on it -- I'm ashamed to say that everything I do now seems to be falling into my lap. Before I am very disdainful to do micro-commerce to sell sports supplements, think this will affect a coach's degree of professionalism, but, these days I re-advertising, or life is forced.
Funny thing is, my mom found out I was delivering food and said, if you're a rider, you can come back home and do it. My hometown is in Hengyang City of Hunan Province under the small county of Foshan of course, I am not a obedient mother of people, even if I go back, I would choose Changsha.
When I'm too old to be a trainer, it might be a good idea to consider becoming a full-time rider.

I'm kind of a slow starter. When I was a fitness instructor, I found it hard to talk to strangers.
There are two types of trainers: A personal trainer who has to speak as if he were selling his skills, and a group drill instructor who earns more than 100 dollars per class. I got into this business purely as a The Wrong Mans, and at first I didn't know anything about it, except that I liked to work out with my hands, and I just kept going online. Later, I went to the fitness institute to learn how to do a personal trainer, how to lead the group calisthenics, learned for 2 months, to apply for the coach.
There are hundreds of gyms in Guangzhou. Before I went to work, I joined a part-time group of group gymnastics coaches. Many gyms would recruit group gymnastics coaches to take classes there. As soon as I saw the recruitment information, I took a job and rode the subway all over Guangzhou. It can be said that I have been to almost all of the 154 stations of the 11 subways in Guangzhou.
Working in the gym, I can exercise every day, I am very happy, the only thing is not good, I do not do sales, it may be too little experience with me, and also do not know what communication skills, always sell classes.
But the only way to survive at the gym is to sell. It's a lot of pressure without results. The company also has a ranking, top ranked colleagues, a month can have one hundred thousand results, while I have only a little, and sometimes will be named and criticized by the leadership. Every day in such an environment, I feel very depressed, in the group exercise class on the stage has become less and less self-confidence.
I know I've been avoiding the sales thing. My hometown in Shaoguan, Guangdong, junior high school did not graduate, I came to Guangzhou to study a secondary technical school, is "computer network applications" , 3 years after graduation, the school introduced me to a telephone sales work. I went over there, stayed for about half a month, and then I realized it wasn't really for me.
I thought I could just do what I love, but I still have to "sell" . Now, this career is essentially a combination of service and sales.
In October last year, I really couldn't do business in the gym. I happened to have a friend who does "digital currency" . I saw the profits were high and quit my job to work with him. I made 50,000 yuan in the first month, but I wasn't happy for long, the next month, it's gone, plus interest.
At that time, I stay at home every day, very decadent, do not know what to do, mind a blank. By January, I was determined to fight it -- but I didn't have a good degree, and I didn't want to be in sales. What could I do?
On second thought, I thought I'd give delivery a try.
In fact, I did not intend to start so early, when the epidemic situation is still very serious, parents do not agree with me to return to Guangzhou early. However, the Dashi Station stationmaster kept calling me, said they are very short of people, I promised my parents, will protect themselves, returned to Guangzhou.

On February 7th, I officially started delivering food, and my internship was for a month. The first day as a rider, Guangzhou felt like an empty city, dark at night, only street lights. Think if it is not an epidemic, the usual evening, there will always be a variety of food stalls on the road, lively.
But this kind of Guangzhou, in the daytime will not affect my mood.
I used to spend every day in the gym, staring at the members, never had a chance to go out, and never thought delivery would be so much fun, as if I were riding around on a little donkey electric bike, looking at all kinds of scenery. Our station is very close to Changlong Zoo, and the view of many residential areas is very good. Sitting on a small donkey blowing river wind, feel comfortable —— This is sitting in the office to blow air-conditioned people can enjoy the joy of a holiday.
Riding around the city on a little donkey scooter
On my first day, however, I lost $20 because one of my meals was not properly secured before delivery and spilled on the way. I told my guest, "I'm sorry. It was a bumpy ride. ". He didn't say anything when he picked up the food, and when I was far away, he called me and said, "it's really hard to eat. ". I compensated him for the original price, after all, this is my personal responsibility, it should be compensated.

Then one day in the evening rush hour, I ran a single ran out of electricity, but this time came two new orders, a vegetable, a pile of cooked vegetables and a large watermelon. I didn't have time to charge it, so I set off on the mule's foot, which slowed me down a lot, and by the time the second order arrived, it was 30 minutes overdue.
Midway, I called the guest three times: The first call did not get through; the second he answered, very impatient, let me hurry; the third call, he was angry, said, "let me go downstairs to look, if the food cold, I will return. ".
When I heard him say this, I felt as if it had been cold for so long. This order is very expensive, I also took a special look at the time of delivery, about 150 yuan. I arrived at the place, and so on the guests downstairs, subliminally touched the take-out bag with his hand, ok, warm, not cold. I said, sir, it's still warm. The guy didn't say anything. He took the takeout. I was relieved.
In this case, if the other party insisted on compensation, I can only admit defeat, because the guests can not understand what kind of emergency you encountered, you stepped on the donkey tired, they do not know.
"It's okay to overtime your internship, and the system won't charge you for it, " Harvard, my master told me. The day before I took up my post, the station master arranged a master for me. I asked him all the questions I didn't understand. Master told me to take one order after another, take your time, get familiar with the route, and above all, "no bad reviews or complaints. ".
I took down the master's words, from the 7th to now, not only no bad comments, but also received several tips, not much money, usually 8.8 or 6.6. It made a lot of sense to me -- as if I'd been at the gym with a member who lost weight and was happier than they were. This is my moment to be valued, to be recognized.
Over the same period before I started or after the beginning of the new trainee riders, have complaints and bad reviews, I can do not, of course, not because I am handsome, but mainly service attitude.
For more than half a month, as I rode through the alley on my mule, I would hear other delivery boys on the phone, and they would say something like this: "Hey, your delivery has arrived, you can come down. " After the guests came down, they handed the delivery to the guests, didn't say anything, just left. After all, I used to be a fitness instructor, in the service industry, and I pay a lot of attention to polite words when communicating with my members. When I talk to guests, I always say things like "thank you" , "enjoy your meal" or "it's been a while" . I also take out the trash for them.
We usually go to work at 10 am and leave at 8 pm. My colleague who started two days before me told me that he only works 8 hours a day, whether he is single or not. But I can't leave at 8:00 every night, and I usually stay up past 10:00. I set myself a small goal -- I'm a Taurus -- to reach 35 a day. I'm always counting my money, and I only make $8,000 at the end of the month if I make 33 a day.
Right now, I'm happy with the way I'm doing my job. I'm sure there are difficulties, but there are more ways. I made more as a rider than I did at the gym. At the peak, I was making 6,000 or 7,000 a month. At the low end, it was just over 4,000. Used to envy others high wages, but very confused, do not know how to do, now every day is very down-to-earth, clear goals, "do" it.
On February 11th, I made my first 35 runs. Lucky for me, I had 41 jobs yesterday. Next month, I'll start my own savings plan, saving at least 5,000 yuan a month.
